xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1466</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">jms-00IX</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00IX.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Finite relations as matrices over the booleans">Finite <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IR.xml"
addr="jms-00IR"
title="Relations and matrices">relations</fr:link> as <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00IS.xml"
addr="jms-00IS"
title="Matrix over a semiring">matrices</fr:link> over the booleans</fr:title><fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The idempotent <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_\mathbb {B}\circ  \operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B}\colon  \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}\to \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex> is in fact the identity function on matrices over the boolean semiring <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {B}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1468</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="machine">#414</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-414.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>17</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00IX</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>We fix a matrix <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M\in \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and compute:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   \begin {aligned}    {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_\mathbb {B}{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}_{i,j}    &=    \begin {cases}    1 &\text {if } i \mathrel {{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} M\right )\mathclose {}}} j\\    0 &\text {otherwise}    \end {cases}    \\    &=    \begin {cases}    1 &\text {if } M_{i,j} = 1\\    0 &\text {otherwise}    \end {cases}   \end {aligned}  ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>Because <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {B}]]></fr:tex> is the boolean semiring, any scalar <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s\in  S]]></fr:tex> is either <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[0]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[1]]></fr:tex>. Therefore, we conclude:</fr:p>

 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_\mathbb {B}{\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {rel}}_\mathbb {B} M\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}_{i,j} = M_{i,j}  ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:p>Thus we conclude that an <html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-matrix</html:span> over the booleans is the same thing as a relation from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
