display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>, an <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-matrix</html:span></fr:strong></fr:em> over a semiring <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (S,0,\oplus ,1,\odot \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is given by entries <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M_{i,j}\in  S]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i\in {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[j\in  {\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. We will write <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {Mat}_{S}{\mathopen {}\left (m,m\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> for the set of <fr:em><fr:strong><html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m\times  n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>-matrices</html:span></fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
